article.description: Andrea Riley scored 31 points to lead No. 21 Oklahoma State to a 100-57 victory against Centenary.
article.headline: Oklahoma State hands Centenary fifth straight loss
article.linkText: Riley powers Oklahoma State rout of Centenary
article.story:
STILLWATER, Okla. -- Andrea Riley scored 31 points to lead No. 21 Oklahoma State to a 100-57 victory against Centenary on Tuesday night.

It was the Cowgirls' 32nd consecutive win at home against a non-conference opponent and sends Oklahoma State (11-2) into Big 12 Conference play this Saturday on an eight-game win streak.

Tegan Cunningham scored 18 points and Megan Byford added a career-high 16 points.

Cierra Bush scored 11 points and had eight rebounds for the Ladies (2-12), who suffered their fifth-straight loss. Natasha Draganic and Ashley Jackson had 10 points apiece.

Centenary outrebounded the Cowgirls 27-24 through one half, but Oklahoma State's pressure defense forced the Ladies into 20 turnovers.

The Cowgirls led 45-24 at the break.
